maxpower.kernel.mem
Class ZeroLatencyMemory<T extends com.maxeler.maxcompiler.v2.kernelcompiler.types.KernelObject<T>>

java.lang.Object
  com.maxeler.maxcompiler.v2.kernelcompiler.KernelLib
      maxpower.kernel.mem.ZeroLatencyMemory<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.maxeler.maxcompiler.v2.kernelcompiler.KernelFinalizer
public class ZeroLatencyMemory<T extends com.maxeler.maxcompiler.v2.kernelcompiler.types.KernelObject<T>>
extends com.maxeler.maxcompiler.v2.kernelcompiler.KernelLib
implements com.maxeler.maxcompiler.v2.kernelcompiler.KernelFinalizer

This memory implementation allows the write() arguments to depend on read() without any stream offset. Data written with write() can be read() immediately on the following cycle. NB: The data written in must be calculated within a single cycle.
